        <svcproc svcproctype="afcrepair">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <svcsubproc>
                <title>Removal</title>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">If equipped with a spotlight on passenger's side, loosen mounting bolt (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690301">Figure 1</hotlnk>) and remove spotlight remote control handle from
                        spotlight shaft. Leave spotlight handle hanging by its wire (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690302">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9690301" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9690301" filename="../afcfigures/g9690301.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 1.</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="f9690302" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9690302" filename="../afcfigures/g9690302.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 2.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Loosen screw on collar and slide collar, wire retainer and rubber spacer off
                        spotlight shaft (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690303">Figure 3</hotlnk>). If required, slide wire through wire retainer to
                        allow it to slide off spotlight shaft. Save collar, wire retainer and rubber spacer for
                        re-installation.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9690303" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9690303" filename="../afcfigures/g9690303.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 3.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Remove 2 mounting screws on outside of cab and remove spotlight. Save for
                        re-installation.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">If equipped with a windshield curtain, remove right side curtain track stop clip (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690304">Figure 4</hotlnk>) and slide right side windshield curtain off and lay
                        it out of the way. Save curtain track stop clip for re-installation.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9690304" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9690304" filename="../afcfigures/g9690304.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 4.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Remove two mounting screws and remove sun visor clip from header trim panel (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690305">Figure 5</hotlnk>). Save screws and clip for re-installation.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9690305" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9690305" filename="../afcfigures/g9690305.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 5.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Remove 4 mounting screws securing interior light to header trim panel (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690306">Figure 6</hotlnk>), drop interior light down and disconnect electrical
                        connector. Save interior light and mounting screws for re-installation.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9690306" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9690306" filename="../afcfigures/g9690306.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 6.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Remove 7 screw covers (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690307">Figure 7</hotlnk>) and snap retainers and mounting screws from header
                        trim panel (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690307">Figure 7</hotlnk>) above passenger door opening. Remove header trim
                        panel. Save screw covers, snap retainers and mounting screws for re-installation.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9690307" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9690307" filename="../afcfigures/g9690307.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 7.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Remove 4 screw covers, then remove snap retainers and mounting screws and remove
                        rear trim panel (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690308">Figure 8</hotlnk>). Save screw covers, snap retainers and mounting
                        screws for re-installation.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9690308" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9690308" filename="../afcfigures/g9690308.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 8.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">If equipped with a windshield curtain use a screwdriver with a 5/16 inch wide bit
                        (max.) and push screwdriver into curtain track retainer above curtain track (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690309">Figure 9</hotlnk>) to spread curtain track retainer apart where stop
                        clip was (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690304">Figure 4</hotlnk>). Push up on screwdriver and pry curtain track out.
                        Pull curtain track down and peel it out of panel (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690310">Figure 10</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9690309" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9690309" filename="../afcfigures/g9690309.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 9.</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="f9690310" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9690310" filename="../afcfigures/g9690310.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 10.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Once curtain track is pulled out of curtain track retainer in the panel, cut curtain
                        track off as near to the center curtain track trim panel as possible (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690311">Figure 11</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9690311" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9690311" filename="../afcfigures/g9690311.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 11.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Slide curtain track out of center curtain track trim panel retainer (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690312">Figure 12</hotlnk>). If necessary use a screwdriver to pry apart
                        curtain track retainer near curve. Be careful not to break the curtain track retainer.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9690312" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9690312" filename="../afcfigures/g9690312.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 12.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Start at right side and remove 3 mounting screws in center curtain track trim panel
                        (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690313">Figure 13</hotlnk>). Save screws for re-installation.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9690313" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9690313" filename="../afcfigures/g9690313.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 13.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Disconnect electrical connector and remove spotlight remote control handle (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690314">Figure 14</hotlnk>). Save for re-installation.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9690314" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9690314" filename="../afcfigures/g9690314.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 14.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Remove mounting screws from the 2 panel angle brackets in the header above door
                        opening (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690315">Figure 15</hotlnk>). Save screws for re-installation.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9690315" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9690315" filename="../afcfigures/g9690315.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 15.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Remove screw cover, snap retainer and mounting screw at the upper right corner of
                        the panel (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690316">Figure 16</hotlnk>). Save screw cover, snap retainer and screw for
                        re-installation.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9690316" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9690316" filename="../afcfigures/g9690316.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 16.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Pull center curtain track trim panel down far enough to pull panel out and place it
                        out of the way (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690317">Figure 17</hotlnk>). If a mounting screw (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690318">Figure 18</hotlnk>) is found under right end of center curtain track
                        trim panel holding panel in place, follow steps below to remove screw.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9690317" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9690317" filename="../afcfigures/g9690317.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 17.</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="f9690318" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9690318" filename="../afcfigures/g9690318.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 18.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Remove 2 screw covers and snap retainers and mounting screws in center header panel
                        (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690319">Figure 19</hotlnk>), as required, to allow access to mounting screw
                        holding panel to be removed (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690318">Figure 18</hotlnk>). Save screws, snap retainers and screw covers for
                        re-installation.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9690319" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9690319" filename="../afcfigures/g9690319.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 19.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Remove 1 mounting screw under right end of center curtain track trim panel (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690318">Figure 18</hotlnk>) and remove panel.
                    </para>
                </step1>
            </svcsubproc>
            <svcsubproc>
                <title>Installation</title>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Remove 4 nylon nuts for the interior light from the old panel and install them in
                        the new panel (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690320">Figure 20</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9690320" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9690320" filename="../afcfigures/g9690320.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 20.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Install interior light with on/off switch at the front and secure with 4 mounting
                        screws (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690321">Figure 21</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9690321" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9690321" filename="../afcfigures/g9690321.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 21.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Use dimensions in
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690322">Figure 22</hotlnk>
                        for the mounting location of the left edge of the new angle brackets.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9690322" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9690322" filename="../afcfigures/g9690322.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 22.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Position the 2 new angle brackets on the new panel (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690323">Figure 23</hotlnk>) with the left edge of the bracket at the location
                        marks (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690322">Figure 22</hotlnk>). Secure with self-drilling screw and snap retainer
                        (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690323">Figure 23</hotlnk>) and install screw cover.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9690323" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9690323" filename="../afcfigures/g9690323.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 23.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Cut upper right rear mounting bracket off 1/2 inch from bottom edge (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690324">Figure 24</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9690324" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9690324" filename="../afcfigures/g9690324.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 24.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Position new panel into the center curtain track trim panel at the front (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690325">Figure 25</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9690325" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9690325" filename="../afcfigures/g9690325.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 25.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Attach the electrical connector to the interior light.</para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Position right rear end panel and right end of panel in place and secure rear end
                        panel to the panel with 2 push-in fasteners (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690326">Figure 26</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9690326" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9690326" filename="../afcfigures/g9690326.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 26.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Position upper right corner of new panel in place and install mounting screw and
                        snap retainer (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690327">Figure 27</hotlnk>). Install screw cover.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9690327" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9690327" filename="../afcfigures/g9690327.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 27.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Push bottom of new panel up against flange on header above door (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690328">Figure 28</hotlnk>) and secure both angle brackets (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690329">Figure 29</hotlnk>) to the header above the door opening with
                        self-drilling screws (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690329">Figure 29</hotlnk>) removed earlier.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9690328" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9690328" filename="../afcfigures/g9690328.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 28.</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="f9690329" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9690329" filename="../afcfigures/g9690329.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 29.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Install 3 mounting screws removed earlier, back in the center curtain track trim
                        panel (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690313">Figure 13</hotlnk>) as required.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">If removed, install snap retainers, mounting screws and screw covers back in the
                        center header panel (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690319">Figure 19</hotlnk>), as required.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Position new header trim panel over the door and align it with top edge of the door
                        opening seal (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690330">Figure 30</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9690330" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9690330" filename="../afcfigures/g9690330.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 30.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Align holes in the new header trim panel for the sun visor clip (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690330">Figure 30</hotlnk>) with holes in the header above the door. Install
                        the sun visor clip and secure it with 2 mounting screws (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690330">Figure 30</hotlnk>) removed earlier.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Hold the new header trim panel in place over the door and install 5 mounting screws,
                        snap retainers and screw covers removed earlier (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690331">Figure 31</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9690331" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9690331" filename="../afcfigures/g9690331.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 31.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Position the new front cove trim cap in place between the windshield and new header
                        trim panel (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690332">Figure 32</hotlnk>). If not equipped with a spotlight, install the 3
                        mounting screws, snap retainers and screw covers (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690332">Figure 32</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9690332" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9690332" filename="../afcfigures/g9690332.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 32.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">If equipped with a spotlight, position the new front cove trim cap in place between
                        the windshield and new header trim panel (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690333">Figure 33</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9690333" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9690333" filename="../afcfigures/g9690333.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 33.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Hold front cove trim cap in position (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690333">Figure 33</hotlnk>) and drill a pilot hole from the outside through
                        the spotlight shaft hole into front cove trim cap.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Use a cutting tool and cut a 1/2 inch hole into cove trim cap from inside (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690333">Figure 33</hotlnk>). Be careful not to tear vinyl covering. If
                        necessary, remove cove trim cap and finish cutting hole.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Connect electrical connector for spotlight remote control handle (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690314">Figure 14</hotlnk>) and position wire behind left end of header trim
                        panel. Leave spotlight handle hanging by its wire.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Position the new front cove trim cap with hole for spotlight shaft back in place
                        between the windshield and new header trim panel (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690334">Figure 34</hotlnk>). Install spotlight shaft through hole in cove trim
                        cap (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690334">Figure 34</hotlnk>) and secure spotlight with 2 mounting screws on
                        outside of cab.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9690334" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9690334" filename="../afcfigures/g9690334.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 34.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Hold new front cove trim cap in position and install the 3 snap retainers, mounting
                        screws and screw covers (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690332">Figure 32</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Install rubber spacer, wire retainer and collar on spotlight shaft. Slide collar
                        against wire retainer and rubber spacer and tighten screw in collar (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690335">Figure 35</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9690335" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9690335" filename="../afcfigures/g9690335.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 35.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Install spotlight remote control handle on spotlight shaft and tighten mounting bolt
                        (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690335">Figure 35</hotlnk>). If required, slide wire through wire retainer to
                        return it to its original position (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690335">Figure 35</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Install 2 nylon nuts into 2 square holes on left side of new rear cove trim panel.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Position left side of new rear cove trim panel in place behind the new rear end
                        panel. Secure rear end panel to rear cove trim panel with 2 snap retainers and mounting screws (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690336">Figure 36</hotlnk>), then install screw covers.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9690336" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9690336" filename="../afcfigures/g9690336.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 36.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Align 2 mounting holes on right side of new rear cove trim panel with existing trim
                        panels. Secure with 2 snap retainers and mounting screws (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690336">Figure 36</hotlnk>), then install screw covers.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">If equipped with a windshield curtain, position new curtain track into curtain track
                        retainer (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690337">Figure 37</hotlnk>). Use a rubber mallet to snap the new curtain track
                        into the new panel and center curtain track trim panel retainers (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690337">Figure 37</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9690337" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9690337" filename="../afcfigures/g9690337.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 37.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Slide the new right side windshield curtain onto the curtain track on the new panel
                        (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690338">Figure 38</hotlnk>). When next to last curtain rollers are installed,
                        slide the new curtain retainer onto the curtain track (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690338">Figure 38</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9690338" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9690338" filename="../afcfigures/g9690338.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 38.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Slide the last curtain rollers onto the curtain track, then install curtain track
                        stop clip (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690339">Figure 39</hotlnk>). Slide the new curtain retainer (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9690338">Figure 38</hotlnk>) and last curtain rollers up against stop clip and
                        tighten retainer screw.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9690339" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g9690339" filename="../afcfigures/g9690339.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                        <caption>Figure 39.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step1>
            </svcsubproc>
